{
  "id": "phekb-nafld-dx",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "nafld",
  "name": "NAFLD - Diagnosis Code Query (Multi-Stage Liver Disease)",
  "description": "**First liver disease phenotype.** Tests ability to find non-alcoholic fatty liver disease patients via diagnosis codes. NAFLD/MASLD is documented under multiple SNOMED codes by histologic stage: hepatic steatosis (simple fatty liver), MASH/NASH (steatohepatitis with inflammation), MASLD (metabolic-associated steatotic liver disease), generic steatohepatitis, and cirrhosis (end-stage). Synthea distributes patients across these stages.",
  "prompt": "Find all patients with a diagnosis of non-alcoholic fatty liver disease, including hepatic steatosis, metabolic-associated steatohepatitis (MASH/NASH), metabolic-associated steatotic liver disease (MASLD), steatohepatitis, and cirrhosis of liver.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all patients with fatty liver disease.",
    "broad": "Find all patients diagnosed with any form of non-alcoholic fatty liver disease \u2014 including simple hepatic steatosis (fatty liver), metabolic-associated steatohepatitis (MASH/NASH \u2014 fatty liver with inflammation), metabolic-associated steatotic liver disease (MASLD \u2014 modern terminology), generic steatohepatitis, and cirrhosis (end-stage liver fibrosis).",
    "expert": "I need to identify all NAFLD/MASLD patients. The condition is documented under multiple SNOMED codes by histologic stage: Steatosis of liver (197321007) is the parent fatty-liver concept, Metabolic dysfunction-associated steatohepatitis (442685003) is MASH/NASH, Metabolic dysfunction-associated steatotic liver (722866000) is MASLD, Steatohepatitis (442191002) is the generic inflammation pattern, and Cirrhosis of liver (19943007) is the end-stage. Search Condition resources for all five codes."
  },
